    "text": "The opaque serial depth metric in statement A includes serial reasoning steps corresponding to the interpretable token bottleneck (discretization into tokens), which adds a multiplicative factor of approximately 28.6 compared to Gemma 4.",
    "topic": "Definition of opaque serial depth with bottleneck"
  },
  {
    "text": "When the opaque serial depth is re-measured without counting the token bottleneck as a serial step, the ratio between DiffusionGemma and Gemma 4 is approximately 1.1, as proposed in statement B.",
    "topic": "Measurement without bottleneck"
  },
  {
    "text": "The near-1.1 ratio without the bottleneck aligns with the finding that DiffusionGemma is similarly monitorable to Gemma 4, while the 28.6 ratio reflects the extra computational cost of converting continuous representations to discrete tokens.",
    "topic": "Reconciliation with existing transparency finding"
  },
  {
    "text": "Future evaluations of opaque serial depth for diffusion language models should explicitly specify whether the tokenization step is counted as a serial operation to avoid contradictory results.",
    "topic": "Standardization of metric"
  }
]
